<pre class="bz_comment_text">A complete lack of security checking allows any user to change video card settings such as clock speed, memory speed, and fanspeed to values that can crash the system and damage the video card. 

Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1.Do nvclock -m (enter a value unreasonable for your card)
2.Watch X lock up and/or your video card break



Actual Results:  
The system crashed.

